{"title_page": "Port of \u0130zmir", "text_new": "{{Infobox port\n| name               = Port of \u0130zmir\n| image              = Martine A in Izmir 20110708 a.jpg\n| image_size         = 250px\n| caption            = \n| country            = [[Turkey]]\n| location           = [[Konak, \u0130zmir|Konak]], [[\u0130zmir]]\n| coordinates        = {{Coord|38|26|32|N|27|09|09|E|type:landmark_region:TR|display=inline,title}}\n| locode             = TRIZM\n| opened             = 1959\n| operated           = [[Turkish State Railways]]\n| owner              = Turkish State Railways\n| type               = Natural\n| sizewater          = \n| sizeland           = {{convert|902000|m2}}<ref name=\"ozellestirme\"/>\n| size               = \n| berths             = \n| wharfs             = \n| piers              = \n| draft_depth        = \n| air_draft          = \n| employees          = 753 (2006)<ref name=\"ozellestirme\"/>\n| leadershiptitle    = Chief Executive Officer\n| leader             = Nihat Kaynar\n| arrivals           = {{decrease}} 2,047 (2018)<ref>{{Cite web | url = https://atlantis.udhb.gov.tr/istatistik/istatistik_gemi.aspx | title = Gemi \u0130statistikleri | publisher = Deniz Ticareti Genel M\u00fcd\u00fcrl\u00fc\u011f\u00fc | accessdate = 6 May 2018 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20180506173651/https://atlantis.udhb.gov.tr/istatistik/istatistik_gemi.aspx | archivedate = 6 May 2018}}</ref>\n| cargotonnage       = {{decrease}} 9,040,779 [[tonne]]s (2018)<ref name=\"yuk\">{{Cite web | url = https://atlantis.udhb.gov.tr/istatistik/istatistik_yuk.aspx | title = Y\u00fck \u0130statistikleri | publisher = Deniz Ticareti Genel M\u00fcd\u00fcrl\u00fc\u011f\u00fc | accessdate = 6 May 2018 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20180507003408/https://atlantis.udhb.gov.tr/istatistik/istatistik_yuk.aspx | archivedate = 7 May 2018}}</ref>\n| containervolume    = {{decrease}} 610,908 [[Twenty-foot equivalent unit|TEU]] (2018)<ref name=\"hacim\">{{Cite web | url = https://atlantis.udhb.gov.tr/istatistik/istatistik_konteyner.aspx | title = Konteyner \u0130statistikleri | publisher = Deniz Ticareti Genel M\u00fcd\u00fcrl\u00fc\u011f\u00fc | accessdate = 6 May 2018 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20180507003123/https://atlantis.udhb.gov.tr/istatistik/istatistik_konteyner.aspx | archivedate = 7 May 2018}}</ref>\n| cargovalue         = \n| passengertraffic   = {{decrease}} 9,172 (2017)<ref>{{Cite web | url = https://atlantis.udhb.gov.tr/istatistik/istatistik_kruvaziyer.aspx | title = Kruvaziyer \u0130statistikleri | publisher = Deniz Ticareti Genel M\u00fcd\u00fcrl\u00fc\u011f\u00fc | accessdate = 6 May 2018 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20180507003252/https://atlantis.udhb.gov.tr/istatistik/istatistik_kruvaziyer.aspx | archivedate = 7 May 2018}}</ref>\n| profit             = [[Turkish lira|\u20ba]]383.2 million (2018)<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/ekonomi/izmir-limaninin-cekim-gucu-artiyor-41155446 |title=\u0130zmir Liman\u0131'n\u0131n '\u00e7ekim' g\u00fcc\u00fc art\u0131yor |work=H\u00fcrriyet |date=20 March 2019 |accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref>\n| website            = \n}}\nThe '''Port of \u0130zmir''' ({{lang-tr|\u0130zmir Liman\u0131}}), alternatively known as '''Port of Alsancak''', is a [[seaport]] in [[\u0130zmir]], [[Turkey]]. It is situated in the [[Gulf of \u0130zmir]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.haritamap.com/yer/izmir-limani-konak|title=\u0130zmir Liman\u0131 Nerede Haritas\u0131 Umurbey Mh. Konak Izmir|website=www.haritamap.com|language=tr|access-date=8 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n[[\u0130zmir]] was an important port of the [[Ottoman Empire]] and the first quay was constructed in 1869. The port was constructed between 1955 and 1959.<ref name=\"ozellestirme\">{{Cite web | url = http://www.izto.org.tr/Portals/0/izmir_alsancak_limani_ve_ozellestirme_sureci.pdf | title = \u0130zmir Alsancak Liman\u0131 ve \u00d6zelle\u015ftirme S\u00fcreci | first = Hitay | last = Baran | publisher = \u0130zmir Chamber of Commmerce | date = June 2006 | accessdate = 4 May 2018 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150906070004/http://www.izto.org.tr:80/portals/0/izmir_alsancak_limani_ve_ozellestirme_sureci.pdf | archivedate = 6 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url = http://www.izto.org.tr/portals/0/iztogenel/dokumanlar/izmir_limaninin_tarihsel_gelisimi_u_cicek_26.04.2012%2022-21-21.pdf | title = \u0130zmir Liman\u0131'n\u0131n Tarihsel Geli\u015fimi | first = \u00dcmit | last = \u00c7i\u00e7ek | publisher = \u0130zmir Ticaret Odas\u0131 | date = June 2006 | accessdate = 4 May 2018 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20161020040859/http://www.izto.org.tr:80/Portals/0/IztoGenel/Dokumanlar/izmir_limaninin_tarihsel_gelisimi_u_cicek_26.04.2012%2022-21-21.pdf | archivedate = 20 October 2016}}</ref> Its first operator was [[Turkish State Railways]]. In 1960 it was acquired by [[DenizBank]] (a state owned bank responsible for maritime business). On 1 January 1989 it was handed back to Turkish State Railways.<ref>{{Cite web | url = http://izto.org.tr/demo_betanix/uploads/cms/yonetim.ieu.edu.tr/6178_1447764634.pdf | title = \u0130zmir Alsancak Liman\u0131'nda Y\u00fck ve Gemi Hizmet Olanaklar\u0131n\u0131n Geli\u015ftirilmesi | first1 = Ersel Zafer | last1 = Oral | first2 = Ayhan | last2 = \u00d6zerden | publisher = \u0130zmir Chamber of Commerce | date = June 2010 | accessdate = 4 May 2018}}</ref> In 2007 it was privatized. But because of legal reasons the privatization was halted. In March 2017, it became a sister port of the [[Port of Miami]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.aa.com.tr/tr/turkiye/izmir-alsancak-limani-ile-miami-limani-kardes-liman-oldu/773307 |title=\u0130zmir Alsancak Liman\u0131 ile Miami Liman\u0131 karde\u015f liman oldu |first=Yusuf |last=\u015eahbaz |agency=Anadolu Ajans\u0131 |date=16 March 2017 |accessdate=4 May 2018}}</ref> In 2018 the port infrastructure was included in the [[Turkey Wealth Fund]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.turkhabergazetesi.com/haber/alsancak-limani-varlik-fonuna-devredildi/5152|title=Alsancak Liman\u0131 Varl\u0131k Fonu'na devredildi|website=www.turkhabergazetesi.com|language=tr|access-date=8 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Technical details==\nThe total land area is {{convert|902000|m2}}.<ref name=\"ozellestirme\"/> The total quay length is {{convert|3386|m}}. With this length the quay serves for 18 ships. The average depth is {{convert|11|m}}.<ref>[http://www.imo.org.tr/resimler/ekutuphane/pdf/17299_52_54.pdf Chamber of Civil Engineers page {{in lang|tr}}]</ref>\n\n==Business==\nAccording to 2018 figures, the number of marine vessels which visit the port is 2,047. The total trading size in the same year was 9 million tonnes.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{\u0130zmir}}\n{{Ports of Turkey}}\n{{Commons category-inline|Port of \u0130zmir}}\n\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in \u0130zmir]]\n[[Category:Konak District]]\n[[Category:Container terminals]]\n[[Category:Turkish State Railways]]\n[[Category:Gulf of \u0130zmir]]\n[[Category:Ports and harbours of Turkey]]\n[[Category:Ports and harbours of the Aegean Sea]]\n[[Category:1959 establishments in Turkey]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox port\n| name               = Port of \u0130zmir\n| image              = Martine A in Izmir 20110708 a.jpg\n| image_size         = 250px\n| caption            = \n| country            = [[Turkey]]\n| location           = [[Konak, \u0130zmir|Konak]], [[\u0130zmir]]\n| coordinates        = {{Coord|38|26|32|N|27|09|09|E|type:landmark_region:TR|display=inline,title}}\n| locode             = TRIZM\n| opened             = 1959\n| operated           = [[Turkish State Railways]]\n| owner              = Turkish State Railways\n| type               = Natural\n| sizewater          = \n| sizeland           = {{convert|902000|m2}}<ref name=\"ozellestirme\"/>\n| size               = \n| berths             = \n| wharfs             = \n| piers              = \n| draft_depth        = \n| air_draft          = \n| employees          = 753 (2006)<ref name=\"ozellestirme\"/>\n| leadershiptitle    = Chief Executive Officer\n| leader             = Nihat Kaynar\n| arrivals           = {{decrease}} 2,047 (2018)<ref>{{Cite web | url = https://atlantis.udhb.gov.tr/istatistik/istatistik_gemi.aspx | title = Gemi \u0130statistikleri | publisher = Deniz Ticareti Genel M\u00fcd\u00fcrl\u00fc\u011f\u00fc | accessdate = 6 May 2018 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20180506173651/https://atlantis.udhb.gov.tr/istatistik/istatistik_gemi.aspx | archivedate = 6 May 2018}}</ref>\n| cargotonnage       = {{decrease}} 9,040,779 [[tonne]]s (2018)<ref name=\"yuk\">{{Cite web | url = https://atlantis.udhb.gov.tr/istatistik/istatistik_yuk.aspx | title = Y\u00fck \u0130statistikleri | publisher = Deniz Ticareti Genel M\u00fcd\u00fcrl\u00fc\u011f\u00fc | accessdate = 6 May 2018 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20180507003408/https://atlantis.udhb.gov.tr/istatistik/istatistik_yuk.aspx | archivedate = 7 May 2018}}</ref>\n| containervolume    = {{decrease}} 610,908 [[Twenty-foot equivalent unit|TEU]] (2018)<ref name=\"hacim\">{{Cite web | url = https://atlantis.udhb.gov.tr/istatistik/istatistik_konteyner.aspx | title = Konteyner \u0130statistikleri | publisher = Deniz Ticareti Genel M\u00fcd\u00fcrl\u00fc\u011f\u00fc | accessdate = 6 May 2018 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20180507003123/https://atlantis.udhb.gov.tr/istatistik/istatistik_konteyner.aspx | archivedate = 7 May 2018}}</ref>\n| cargovalue         = \n| passengertraffic   = {{decrease}} 9,172 (2017)<ref>{{Cite web | url = https://atlantis.udhb.gov.tr/istatistik/istatistik_kruvaziyer.aspx | title = Kruvaziyer \u0130statistikleri | publisher = Deniz Ticareti Genel M\u00fcd\u00fcrl\u00fc\u011f\u00fc | accessdate = 6 May 2018 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20180507003252/https://atlantis.udhb.gov.tr/istatistik/istatistik_kruvaziyer.aspx | archivedate = 7 May 2018}}</ref>\n| profit             = [[Turkish lira|\u20ba]]383.2 million (2018)<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/ekonomi/izmir-limaninin-cekim-gucu-artiyor-41155446 |title=\u0130zmir Liman\u0131'n\u0131n '\u00e7ekim' g\u00fcc\u00fc art\u0131yor |work=H\u00fcrriyet |date=20 March 2019 |accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref>\n| website            = \n}}\nThe '''Port of \u0130zmir''' ({{lang-tr|\u0130zmir Liman\u0131}}), alternatively known as '''Port of Alsancak''', is a [[seaport]] in [[\u0130zmir]], [[Turkey]]. It is situated in the [[Gulf of \u0130zmir]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.haritamap.com/yer/izmir-limani-konak|title=\u0130zmir Liman\u0131 Nerede Haritas\u0131 Umurbey Mh. Konak Izmir|website=www.haritamap.com|language=tr|access-date=8 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n[[\u0130zmir]] was an important port of the [[Ottoman Empire]] and the first quay was constructed in 1869. The port was constructed between 1955 and 1959.<ref name=\"ozellestirme\">{{Cite web | url = http://www.izto.org.tr/Portals/0/izmir_alsancak_limani_ve_ozellestirme_sureci.pdf | title = \u0130zmir Alsancak Liman\u0131 ve \u00d6zelle\u015ftirme S\u00fcreci | first = Hitay | last = Baran | publisher = \u0130zmir Chamber of Commmerce | date = June 2006 | accessdate = 4 May 2018 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150906070004/http://www.izto.org.tr:80/portals/0/izmir_alsancak_limani_ve_ozellestirme_sureci.pdf | archivedate = 6 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url = http://www.izto.org.tr/portals/0/iztogenel/dokumanlar/izmir_limaninin_tarihsel_gelisimi_u_cicek_26.04.2012%2022-21-21.pdf | title = \u0130zmir Liman\u0131'n\u0131n Tarihsel Geli\u015fimi | first = \u00dcmit | last = \u00c7i\u00e7ek | publisher = \u0130zmir Ticaret Odas\u0131 | date = June 2006 | accessdate = 4 May 2018 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20161020040859/http://www.izto.org.tr:80/Portals/0/IztoGenel/Dokumanlar/izmir_limaninin_tarihsel_gelisimi_u_cicek_26.04.2012%2022-21-21.pdf | archivedate = 20 October 2016}}</ref> Its first operator was [[Turkish State Railways]]. In 1960 it was acquired by [[DenizBank]] (a state owned bank responsible for maritime business). On 1 January 1989 it was handed back to State Railways.<ref>{{Cite web | url = http://izto.org.tr/demo_betanix/uploads/cms/yonetim.ieu.edu.tr/6178_1447764634.pdf | title = \u0130zmir Alsancak Liman\u0131'nda Y\u00fck ve Gemi Hizmet Olanaklar\u0131n\u0131n Geli\u015ftirilmesi | first1 = Ersel Zafer | last1 = Oral | first2 = Ayhan | last2 = \u00d6zerden | publisher = \u0130zmir Chamber of Commerce | date = June 2010 | accessdate = 4 May 2018}}</ref> In 2007 it was privatized. But because of legal reasons the privatization was halted. In March 2017, it became a sister port of the [[Port of Miami]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.aa.com.tr/tr/turkiye/izmir-alsancak-limani-ile-miami-limani-kardes-liman-oldu/773307 |title=\u0130zmir Alsancak Liman\u0131 ile Miami Liman\u0131 karde\u015f liman oldu |first=Yusuf |last=\u015eahbaz |agency=Anadolu Ajans\u0131 |date=16 March 2017 |accessdate=4 May 2018}}</ref> In 2018 the port infrastructure was included in the [[Turkey Wealth Fund]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.turkhabergazetesi.com/haber/alsancak-limani-varlik-fonuna-devredildi/5152|title=Alsancak Liman\u0131 Varl\u0131k Fonu'na devredildi|website=www.turkhabergazetesi.com|language=tr|access-date=8 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Technical details==\nThe total land area is {{convert|902000|m2}}.<ref name=\"ozellestirme\"/> The total quay length is {{convert|3386|m}}. With this length the quay serves for 18 ships. The average depth is {{convert|11|m}}.<ref>[http://www.imo.org.tr/resimler/ekutuphane/pdf/17299_52_54.pdf Chamber of Civil Engineers page {{in lang|tr}}]</ref>\n\n==Business==\nAccording to 2018 figures, the number of marine vessels which visit the port is 2,047. The total trading size in the same year was 9 million tonnes.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{\u0130zmir}}\n{{Ports of Turkey}}\n{{Commons category-inline|Port of \u0130zmir}}\n\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in \u0130zmir]]\n[[Category:Konak District]]\n[[Category:Container terminals]]\n[[Category:Turkish State Railways]]\n[[Category:Gulf of \u0130zmir]]\n[[Category:Ports and harbours of Turkey]]\n[[Category:Ports and harbours of the Aegean Sea]]\n[[Category:1959 establishments in Turkey]]\n", "name_user": "Nedim Ardo\u011fa", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eHistory", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Port_of_%C4%B0zmir"}
