oal with piano - Bremen pianist plays in Hambach Forest|author-first=Serena |author-last=Bilanceri |date=2018-10-06 |series=Buten un binnen ([[:de:Buten un binnen|de]]) |publisher=[[Radio Bremen]] |url=https://www.butenunbinnen.de/nachrichten/gesellschaft/pianisthambacherforst100.html |access-date=2018-10-07}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Stop_2018\">{{cite web |title=Ablauf und Programm - Kundgebungsprogramm 10.30 \u2013 16 Uhr. Im Anschluss gibt es bis 19 Uhr ein Musikprogramm. |language=de |date=2018-10-06 |publisher=Stop Kohle |url=https://www.stop-kohle.de/ablauf-2/ |access-date=2019-09-15 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190915203856/https://www.stop-kohle.de/ablauf-2/ |archive-date=2019-09-15}} (NB. This announcement does not reflect the chronological order of appearance of speakers and musicians on stage. Also, there have been some last minute changes compared to the list of announced participants. The article only lists people who actually took part in the event.)</ref>\n<ref name=\"Golden_2019\">{{cite news |url=https://www.tellerreport.com/life/golden-camera-for-greta.BkN8QDaOV.html |title=Agiamo Golden Camera for Greta |publisher=International News |date=2019-03-30 |access-date=2019-06-22}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Thunberg_2019\">{{cite news |author-last=Graham-Harrison |author-first=Emma |title=Greta Thunberg takes climate fight to Germany's threatened Hambach Forest |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |date=2019-08-10 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2019/aug/10/greta-thunberg-climate-change-fight-germany-hambach-forest |access-date=2019-09-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190912045758/https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2019/aug/10/greta-thunberg-climate-change-fight-germany-hambach-forest |archive-date=2019-09-12}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"M\u00fcllender_2018\">{{cite news |title=Proteste im Hambacher Forst - Prozess gegen Kohlegegner gestoppt - Nach sieben Wochen U-Haft: Aktivisten des Hambacher Forsts kommen frei. Der Prozessauftakt scheitert wegen Schlamperei der Beh\u00f6rden. |author-first=Bernd |author-last=M\u00fcllender |date=2018-03-16 |newspaper=[[Die Tageszeitung]] (taz) |language=de |location=Kerpen / Aachen, Germany |url=https://taz.de/Proteste-im-Hambacher-Forst/!5492067/ |access-date=2019-09-20 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180324070313/https://taz.de/Proteste-im-Hambacher-Forst/!5492067/ |archive-date=2018-03-24}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Pauli_2018\">{{cite news |title=Umweltaktivist vom Hambacher Forst zu Haftstrafe verurteilt |author-first=Christoph |author-last=Pauli |date=2018-03-30 |newspaper=[[Aachener Zeitung]] (AZ) |language=de |location=Kerpen, Germany |url=https://www.aachener-zeitung.de/nrw-region/umweltaktivist-vom-hambacher-forst-zu-haftstrafe-verurteilt_aid-24476103 |access-date=2019-09-20 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190920221211/https://www.aachener-zeitung.de/nrw-region/umweltaktivist-vom-hambacher-forst-zu-haftstrafe-verurteilt_aid-24476103 |archive-date=2019-09-20}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Gego_2019\">{{cite news |title=Prozess gegen Hambacher-Forst-Aktivistin: Im Zweifel f\u00fcr die australische Angeklagte |author-first=Marlon |author-last=Gego |date=2019-05-14 |newspaper=[[Aachener Zeitung]] (AZ) |language=de |location=Cologne, Germany |url=https://www.aachener-zeitung.de/nrw-region/braunkohle/am-mittwoch-faellt-das-urteil-ueber-eine-waldbesetzerin-aus-australien_aid-38783397 |access-date=2019-09-20 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190920222614/https://www.aachener-zeitung.de/nrw-region/braunkohle/am-mittwoch-faellt-das-urteil-ueber-eine-waldbesetzerin-aus-australien_aid-38783397 |archive-date=2019-09-20}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"SPON-1231326\">{{cite web |title=Letzte Baumh\u00e4user ger\u00e4umt: RWE bereitet Rodung im Hambacher Forst vor |language=de |author-first= |author-last= |work=[[Spiegel Online]] |date=2018-10-02 |url=http://www.spiegel.de/wirtschaft/soziales/hambacher-forst-rwe-bereitet-rodung-vor-a-1231326.html |access-date=2018-10-03 |url-status=live |archive-url= |archive-date=}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"VGK\u00f6ln_2017\">Verwaltungsgericht K\u00f6ln (Administrative Court Cologne), Court order of 2017-11-24 (14 K 1282/15)</ref>\n<ref name=\"RegArnsberg_2018\">{{cite web |title=Tagebau Hambach - Hauptbetriebsplan f\u00fcr den Zeitraum 01.04.2018 bis 31.12.2020 |type=Letter of decision |language=de |date=2018-03-29 |author= |publisher=Bezirksregierung Arnsberg |location=Dortmund, Germany |page=24 |url=https://www.bezreg-arnsberg.nrw.de/presse/2018/03/063_18_03_29/2018-03-29-Zulassung-HBP-2018-2020.pdf |access-date=2019-09-21 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190301135300/https://www.bezreg-arnsberg.nrw.de/presse/2018/03/063_18_03_29/2018-03-29-Zulassung-HBP-2018-2020.pdf |archive-date=2019-03-01}} (53 pages)</ref>\n}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Commons category-inline|Hambacher Forst}}\n\n{{coord|50.9074|N|6.4488|E|source:wikidata|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Forests and woodlands of North Rhine-Westphalia]]\n[[Category:Old growth forests]]\n[[Category:Environmental issues in Germany]]\n[[Category:Squats in Germany]]\n", "text_old": "{{Expand German|Hambacher Forst|date=February 2017}}\n<!-- for as long as this article doesn't cover most aspects of the German Wikipedia articles about the topic -->\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2019|cs1-dates=y}}\n[[File:Hambacher Forst Herbst 2018.jpg|thumb|Aerial view of Hambach Forest from the south, October 2018]]\n'''Hambach Forest''' ({{lang-de|Hambacher Wald, Hambacher Forst, B\u00fcrgewald, Die B\u00fcrge}}) is an ancient forest located near {{ill|Buir (Kerpen){{!}}Buir|de|Buir (Kerpen)}} in [[North Rhine-Westphalia]], western Germany, between Cologne and Aachen. It is planned to be cleared as part of the [[Hambach surface mine]] by owner [[RWE AG]]. There have been ongoing protests and occupations to prevent this since 2012.\n\n[[File:Cut forest digger in bkgrd.jpg|thumb|Area of destroyed forest with excavator]]\n[[File:Hambach surface mine and Hambach Forest.png|thumb|[[Hambach surface mine]] ({{color|gray}}); remaining '''Hambach Forest''' in the south (NE of Morschenich ([[:de:Morschenich|de]])); recultivated [[Sophienh\u00f6he]] in NW, 2017<ref name=\"Map_2017\"/>]]\n\n== The forest ==\n[[File:Myotis_bechsteinii-flying1.jpg|thumb|Hambach Forest's rare [[Bechstein's bat]] population is threatened.]]\nHambach Forest is rich in biodiversity and home to 142 species regarded as important for conservation.\nThe forest has been called ''\"the last remnant of a sylvan ecosystem that has occupied this part of the Rhine River plain between Aachen and Cologne since the end of the last ice age\"''.<ref name=\"Doomed_2018\"/> Only ten percent of Hambach Forest still remains, and the remaining forest is severely threatened by mining for brown coal.<ref name=\"Doomed_2018\"/> Of special interest is the rare [[Bechstein's bat]] population, which is strictly protected according to annex II and annex IV of the European [[Habitats Directive]].<ref name=\"BAT_2018\"/>\nAn [[Environmental Impact Assessment]] study has never been conducted. The {{ill|Administrative Court Cologne{{!}}Administrative Court|de|Verwaltungsgericht K\u00f6ln}} in [[Cologne]] denied the necessity of such a study in November 2017 because the permission for the mining operations was given in the 1970s, long before Environmental Impact Assessment studies became mandatory.<ref name=\"VGK\u00f6ln_2017\"/><ref name=\"RegArnsberg_2018\"/>\n\n[[File:Rheinisches Braunkohlerevier DE.png|thumb|Lignite mining in the area, as of 2018. [[Hambach surface mine|Hambach pit mine]] is left of center.]]\n\n== Lignite mining ==\n{{main|Hambach surface mine}}\nThe area is part of the ''Rhenish Lignite Mining Area'' ({{lang-de|Rheinisches Braunkohlerevier}} ([[:de:Rheinisches Braunkohlerevier|de]])), and the [[Hambach surface mine]] is the largest open pit mine in Germany, as of 2018. [[RWE AG]] has owned the land since the 1960s or earlier and has held an official permit to clear forests in the area since the 1970s. The company has repeatedly argued that Hambach Forest must be cleared to ensure future energy supply. RWE spokesperson Guido Steffen states \u201cI\u2019ve known Hambach for decades, before the mine. It was a great forest ... It\u2019s a pity it must be logged. We\u2019re not doing this because we have fun logging trees, but out of economic necessity. Germany needs energy.\u201d<ref name=\"Doomed_2018\"/> \n\nThe usual process is to excavate the lignite/brown coal beneath it with huge excavator machines and then burn it in [[steam-electric power generation]]. The 2018 map to the right shows the extent of excavation activities until then. On this map, Hambach Forest (around abandoned old Morschenich) is not displayed at all, but under a hatching meaning \"future area of operations\".\n\n== First occupations by environmentalists (2012\u20132014) ==\nSince 2012, Hambach Forest has been a political standpoint for environmentalists who are protesting against the German energy company [[RWE AG]] because of the open-pit [[Hambach surface mine]] neighboring the site. At 33 square miles, the mine is the largest of its kind in Europe.<ref name=\"Doomed_2018\"/><ref name=\"DW_2016\"/>\n\nAn area within the forest was occupied by those opposing the clearance for lignite extraction. They sought to close the mine and save the remaining sections of the forest which are under threat of being cut down to allow the expansion of the mine.\n\nThe first occupation lasted from April to November 2012. A second occupation started in September 2013 and lasted until March 2014, followed by a third occupation from April to October 2014.{{r|rep}}\n\n[[File:Hangingbarricade (27065382544).jpg|thumb|Barricade (September 2016)]]\n\n== Fourth occupation (2015\u20132018) ==\nThe fourth occupation period started in 2015<!-- some sources state 2014 --> and lasted until 2018. It involved a settlement with around two dozen [[tree house]]s and numerous [[road barricade]]s. The barricades were erected to prevent mining company and police vehicles from entering.<ref name=\"rep\"/>\n\n=== BUND lawsuit and court order ===\nCutting seasons last from 1 October until the end of February and usually 70-80 [[hectare]]s are cleared in each period. The tree cutting operations in the 2017/2018 cutting season ended after just two days in November 2017, after the {{ill|Higher Administrative Court North-Rhine Westphalia{{!}}Higher Administrative Court|de|Oberverwaltungsgericht f\u00fcr das Land Nordrhein-Westfalen}} in [[M\u00fcnster]] ordered a halt. According to [[BUND]], the environmental protection association that filed the corresponding lawsuit, Hambach Forest, with its [[Quercus robur|common oak]], [[hornbeam]] and [[lily of the valley]] populations, is a habitat of type 9160 of annex I of the European [[Habitats Directive]] (Council Directive 92/43/EEC of 21 May 1992).<ref name=\"Bund_2017\"/>\nOf special interest in this lawsuit was the [[Bechstein's bat]], which is strictly protected according to annex II and annex IV of the European [[Habitats Directive]].<ref name=\"BAT_2018\"/>\n\n=== Arrests of activists (spring of 2018) ===\n[[File:Gemeinsam stark,Hambacher Forst,NRW.jpg|thumb|Colony of tree houses in Hambach Forest (February 2018)]]\nOn 22 January 2018, nine Hambach Forest activists were arrested for resisting a barricade eviction. All of the arrested refused to give any details about their identities and remained unknown in pretrial detention and also in the courtroom.<ref name=\"M\u00fcllender_2018\"/>\nOne activist, who was freed from a [[Lock-on (protest tactic)|lock-on]] on a [[tripod]], was sentenced to 6 months on parole after a pretrial detention of 67 days in {{ill|JVA Cologne{{!}}Cologne-Ossendorf jail|de|Justizvollzugsanstalt K\u00f6ln}}.<ref name=\"Pauli_2018\"/><ref name=\"M\u00fcllender_2018\"/>\nTwo activists were released after 52 days in pretrial detention in Cologne-Ossendorf jail after a medical examination revealed that they were most probably under 21 years old and should therefore be processed under juvenile law.<ref name=\"M\u00fcllender_2018\"/>\n\nA 22 year old activist from Australia joined the occupation in March 2018 and planned to stay for two weeks also in order to take part in a workshop to build tree houses. She had been arrested on 19 March one week after her arrival after she had been part of a group out of which firecrackers were thrown in the direction of police officers.<ref name=\"Gego_2019\"/>\nShe decided not to give any personal details and tried to stay anonymously.<ref name=\"Gego_2019\"/> As a consequence she had been taken into pretrial detention (as \"Unknown Person III\" [UP III]), denying herself the chance to take her already booked flight back home to Australia one week later.<ref name=\"Gego_2019\"/> According to the prosecutor she was identified one day before her trial which took place on 31 July 2018.<ref name=\"Gego_2019\"/> She has been sentenced to 9 months in prison without parole.<ref name=\"Gego_2019\"/>\nAfter a court hearing on 4 October she has been released.<ref name=\"Gego_2019\"/>\n\n[[File:Barrikaden in der B\u00fcrge.jpg|thumb|Newly erected barricades (September 2018)]]\n\n=== Police clearing the tree houses (September 2018) ===\n{{See also|:de:R\u00e4umung des Hambacher Forsts 2018{{!}}Eviction of Hambach Forest 2018&nbsp;(German)}}\nOn 13 September 2018 a large scale police operation started initiated by North Rhine-Westphalian Ministry of Construction to evict more than fifty tree houses which existed for up to six years because they didn't comply with fire safety regulation standards.\nTo protect life and limb of the tree house occupants was announced as an important goal of the operation.<ref name=\"AF_2018\"/>\n\n=== Journalist falls and dies ===\nAs evictions continued, on 19 September 2018, the 27-year old artist, blogger and journalist Steffen Meyn fell through a [[Canopy walkway|walkway]] of 15 meters height in the treehouse village of Beechtown and died. Meyn was working on a long-time documentary project of the activities in the Hambach Forest. Immediate resuscitation efforts failed.<ref name=\"taz_2018\"/> \n\nThe eviction of tree houses was  stopped immediately after that incident by [[Herbert Reul]], North Rhine-Westphalia's interior minister. He said \"We cannot just proceed as normal \u2014 at least I can't.\"<ref name=\"Wecker_2018\"/>\n\nThe eviction proceedings resumed on 23 September 2018. According to a police statement all 86 tree houses had been evicted and destroyed on 2 October 2018.<ref name=\"SPON-1231326\"/>\n\n== Current occupation (2018\u2013&nbsp;) ==\n=== Court order stops clearance again (October 2018) ===\nOn 5 October 2018 the Higher Administrative Court ({{lang-de|Oberverwaltungsgericht}} ([[:de:Oberverwaltungsgericht|de]])) of [[M\u00fcnster]] ruled that the clearance of Hambach Forest by [[RWE AG|RWE]] has to stop immediately until evidence brought by [[BUND]] can be evaluated.<ref name=\"CNN_2018\"/> The evidence in question concerns the threat to the local [[Bechstein's bat]] population.<ref name=\"Tagesschau_2018\"/> The final court decision is expected for 2020.<ref name=\"Tagesschau_2018-10-06\"/> Activists started to build new tree houses again.\n\n=== {{anchor|20181006}}Large demonstration (October 2018) ===\n[[File:Hambacher Forst, Demonstration 6. Oktober 2018 01.jpg|thumb|Demonstration ''Wald retten \u2013 Kohle stoppen!'' near Hambacher Forst (6&nbsp;October 2018)]]\nOn 6 October 2018 there was a large [[Demonstration (protest)|demonstration]] \"{{lang|de|Wald retten \u2013 Kohle stoppen!}}\" (English: \"Save the forest \u2013 Stop coal!\") near Hambach Forest. It was organized by [[BUND]], {{ill|Campact|de}}, [[Greenpeace]], [[NaturFreunde Deutschlands]] ([[Friends of Nature]]), the local initiatives {{lang|de|Buirer f\u00fcr Buir}} and {{lang|de|Arbeitsgemeinschaft \"B\u00e4uerliche Landwirtschaft\"}} (AbL), and others.<ref name=\"AN_2018\"/><ref name=\"BUND_2018\"/><ref name=\"RP_2018\"/> Originally planned for {{val|5000}} people, and with {{val|25000}} people anticipated before the event was temporarily forbidden two days earlier, there were {{val|50000}} participants according to the organizers;<ref name=\"AN_2018\"/> the police acknowledged some {{val|25000}} to {{val|30000}}. The demonstrators celebrated the recent court decision in a peaceful festival atmosphere with many speeches, demanding an end to the use of coal to generate power.<ref name=\"AN_2018\"/><ref name=\"BUND_2018\"/><ref name=\"DW_2018\"/> Participating speakers included <!-- exact chronological order still to be sorted out -->{{ill|Michael M\u00fcller (politician, 1948){{!}}Michael M\u00fcller|de|Michael M\u00fcller (Politiker, 1948)}} (NaturFreunde Deutschlands),<ref name=\"Stop_2018\"/><ref name=\"DW_2018\"/><ref name=\"BUND_2018\"/><!-- unconfirmed: Momo (activist),<ref name=\"Stop_2018\"/>--> Jens Sannig (pastor),<ref name=\"RP_2018\"/> Ulf Allhoff-Cramer ([[Detmold]] farmer),<ref name=\"Stop_2018\"/> {{ill|Antje Grothus|de}} (Buirer f\u00fcr Buir),<ref name=\"Stop_2018\"/><ref name=\"AN_2018\"/><ref name=\"BUND_2018\"/> {{ill|Hubert Weiger|de}} (BUND),<ref name=\"Stop_2018\"/><ref name=\"AN_2018\"/><ref name=\"BUND_2018\"/><ref name=\"RP_2018\"/><!-- unconfirmed: {{ill|Kathrin Henneberger|de}} ([[Ende Gel\u00e4nde 2018|Ende Gel\u00e4nde]])<ref name=\"Stop_2018\"/> --> Martin Kaiser (Greenpeace),<ref name=\"Stop_2018\"/><ref name=\"AN_2018\"/><ref name=\"BUND_2018\"/><ref name=\"RP_2018\"/> Mamadou Mbodji ([[NaturFreunde Internationale]]),<ref name=\"Stop_2018\"/> Helene Nietert (Camp for Future),<ref name=\"Stop_2018\"/><ref name=\"AN_2018\"/> {{ill|Christoph Bautz|de|Christoph Bautz (Aktivist)}} (Campact),<ref name=\"Stop_2018\"/><ref name=\"BUND_2018\"/><ref name=\"Ludwig_2018\"/> {{ill|Jochen Flasbarth|de}} ([[Federal Ministry of the Environment, Nature Conservation and Nuclear Safety|BMU]]),<ref name=\"Stop_2018\"/> [[Annalena Baerbock]] ([[B\u00fcndnis 90/Die Gr\u00fcnen]]),<ref name=\"Stop_2018\"/><ref name=\"AN_2018\"/> [[Bernd Riexinger]]<!-- and Lorenz G\u00f6sta Beutin? --> ([[The Left (Germany)|Die Linke]]),<ref name=\"Stop_2018\"/> Michael Zobel ([[forest educator]]),<ref name=\"Stop_2018\"/> Ingo Bajerke ({{ill|Keyenberg|de}}),<ref name=\"Stop_2018\"/><ref name=\"Ludwig_2018\"/><!-- unconfirmed: Isabell Braunger ([[German Institute for Economic Research|DIW]])<ref name=\"Stop_2018\"/> --> {{ill|Uwe Hiksch|de}} (Naturfreunde),<ref name=\"RP_2018\"/> and Milan Schwarze ([[Ende Gel\u00e4nde 2018|Ende Gel\u00e4nde]]).<ref name=\"Ludwig_2018\"/> Various musicians supported the event with live performances including {{ill|Eddi H\u00fcnecke|de|Edzard H\u00fcneke}},<ref name=\"Stop_2018\"/> [[Revolverheld]],<ref name=\"Stop_2018\"/><ref name=\"AN_2018\"/><ref name=\"BUND_2018\"/><ref name=\"RP_2018\"/><ref name=\"Ludwig_2018\"/> {{ill|Tonbandger\u00e4t|de|Tonbandger\u00e4t (Band)}},<ref name=\"Stop_2018\"/><ref name=\"Ludwig_2018\"/><!-- announced, but not confirmed by any photo/video on site: {{ill|Cat Ballou (band){{!}}Cat Ballou|de|Cat Ballou}},<ref name=\"Stop_2018\"/><ref name=\"Ludwig_2018\"/> --> [[Die H\u00f6chste Eisenbahn]],<ref name=\"Stop_2018\"/> {{ill|Gerd Schinkel|de}},<ref name=\"Stop_2018\"/> <!-- \"my traveling piano\" -->{{ill|Joe L\u00f6hrmann|de}},<ref name=\"Bilanceri_2018_L\u00f6hrmann\"/> [[Davide Martello]],<ref name=\"Zeit_2018\"/><ref name=\"BUND_2018\"/> and <!-- Samba percussion group from Koblenz -->Piri-Piri.<ref name=\"Zeit_2018\"/>\n\n{{Panorama|image=File:Abbruchkante mit Schaufelradbagger am Hambacher Forst (Panorama1).jpg|height=250|caption=Panorama of [[Hambach open-pit lignite mine]] in the neighbourhood of the Hambach Forest showing a protest banner and a [[bucket-wheel excavator]] on {{nowrap|{{date|2018-10-06|dmy}}}}|dir=ltr}}\n\n=== 2019 ===\nWhen [[Greta Thunberg]] was awarded the [[Goldene Kamera|Golden Camera Award]] in March 2019, she dedicated the prize to those protecting the Hambach Forest.<ref name=\"Golden_2019\"/> She then visited the site, saying \"It makes me incredibly sad, to see all this destruction, in this area that used to be a forest ecosystem, and I feel sorry for the people who have to move.\"<ref name=\"Thunberg_2019\"/>\n\n=== 2020===\nIn January 2020, the preservation of the Hambach Forest was agreed at a top-level meeting of the German government and the four federal states affected by the coal phase-out. However the \"Roadmap for Coal Phase-out\" does not yet have the character of a law.<ref>{{cite web |author=<!--Not stated--> |url=https://www.tagesschau.de/wirtschaft/kohleausstieg-bund-laender-einigung-103.html |title=Kohle-Unternehmen erhalten Milliarden |publisher=Tagesschau.de |date=2020-01-16 |access-date=2020-01-16 }}}</ref>\n\n== Gallery ==\n<gallery caption=\"Views from within Hambach Forest\" widths=\"200px\" perrow=\"2\">\nImage:Hambacher Forst bei Morschenich DE 2018-09-09 F.jpg|near Morschenich ([[:de:Morschenich|de]])<br />September 2018\nImage:Hambacher Forst 2016 LBA 4703.jpg|unknown location, February 2016\n</gallery>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Ende Gel\u00e4nde 2017]]\n* [[Ende Gel\u00e4nde 2018]]\n* [[September 2019 climate strikes]]\n* {{ill|Morschenich|de}}\n* {{ill|Manheim (Kerpen)|de|Manheim}}\n* {{ill|Hambach (Niederzier)|de}}\n* [[Arnold of Arnoldsweiler]]\n* [[Sophienh\u00f6he]]\n* {{ill|Hambach industrial spur|de|Hambachbahn}}\n* [[Fossil fuel phase-out]]\n* [[Commission on Growth, Structural Change and Employment]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n<ref name=\"BAT_2018\">{{cite web |title=Endangered species |url=https://hambachforest.org/background/the-forest/endangered-species/#VespertilionDeBechstein |website=Hambach Forest |access-date=2019-09-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190522224301/https://hambachforest.org/background/the-forest/endangered-species/#VespertilionDeBechstein |archive-date=2019-05-22}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Doomed_2018\">{{cite web |url=https://news.nationalgeographic.com/2018/04/hambach-forest-germany-logging-coal-conservation-science |title=Ancient Forest Home of Squatter Communities Is Doomed by Coal |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190914181247/https://www.nationalgeographic.com/news/2018/04/hambach-forest-germany-logging-coal-conservation-science/ | archive-date=14 September 2019 | date=13 April 2018 |publisher=[[National Geographic]]}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Map_2017\">{{cite web|url=https://hambachforest.org/blog/2017/11/28/action-map-of-the-wood |title=Action Map of the Wood \u2013 Hambach Forest|publisher=}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"DW_2016\">{{cite web |url=http://www.dw.com/en/clash-in-german-forest-as-red-line-is-crossed/a-36606405 |title=Clash in German forest as red line is crossed |work=DW Environment |date=2016-12-01 |publisher=[[Deutsche Welle]] (DW)}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Bund_2017\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bund-nrw.de/fileadmin/nrw/dokumente/braunkohle/2017_11_BUND-Background_Hambacher_Forst_EN.pdf |title=Save the \"Hambacher Forst\" - Stop coal mining |publisher=[[BUND]] - Friends of the Earth Germany |access-date=2018-04-15}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Wecker_2018\">{{cite news |author-last=Wecker |author-first=Katharina |title=Stillness and shock in Hambach Forest after journalist dies |url=https://www.dw.com/en/stillness-and-shock-in-hambach-forest-after-journalist-dies/a-45579629 |access-date=2019-09-14 |publisher=[[Deutsche Welle]] (DW) |date=2018-09-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190513125300/https://www.dw.com/en/stillness-and-shock-in-hambach-forest-after-journalist-dies/a-45579629 |archive-date=2019-05-13}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"taz_2018\">{{cite news |title=Tod im Hambacher Forst - Vom Beobachter zum Freund|trans-title=Death in Hambach Forest - From observer to friend |language=de |date=2018-09-20 |publisher=[[Die Tageszeitung]] (taz) |u