 Ellis<br>{{flagicon|AUS}} John Lusty\n| [[Holden VL Commodore SS Group A]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 120\n|- \n! 13\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| C\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 31 <ref>Quinn, Faulkner, Price & Smith were all entered in both car 31 & car 32 (as per Official Program). Car 31 placed 13th (as per touringcarracing.net). Quinn & Faulkner drove the 13th placed car (as per Auto Action).</ref>\n| [[Toyota Team Australia]]\n| {{flagicon|AUS}} Mike Quinn<br>{{flagicon|NZL}} [[John Faulkner (racing driver)|John Faulkner]]\n| [[Toyota Corolla (E90)|Toyota Corolla]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 119\n|- \n! 14\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| A\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 29\n| Mulvihill Motorsports Pty Ltd <ref name=touringcarracing.net>[http://touringcarracing.net/Races/1987%20Sandown%20Castrol.html Castrol 500, touringcarracing.net] Retrieved 15 March 2016</ref>\n| {{flagicon|AUS}} Tony Mulvihill<br>{{flagicon|AUS}} Ken Matthews\n| [[Holden VK Commodore SS Group A]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 119\n|- \n! 15\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| B\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 78\n| B Bolwell \n| {{flagicon|AUS}} Brian Bolwell<br>{{flagicon|AUS}} Rod Smith\n| [[BMW E30|BMW 323i]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 117\n|- \n! 16\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| B\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 24\n| Lockwood Bryce Homes\n| {{flagicon|AUS}} Bill Bryce<br>{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Leo Geoghegan]]\n| [[BMW 3 Series (E30)|BMW 325i]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 116\n|- \n! 17\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| A \n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 20\n| Salisbury North Service Station\n| {{flagicon|AUS}} Des Wall<br>{{flagicon|AUS}} John Virgo\n| [[BMW E24|BMW 635 CSi]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 116\n|- \n! 18\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| A\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 21\n| Lusty Engineering Pty Ltd\n| {{flagicon|AUS}} Graham Lusty<br>{{flagicon|AUS}} Ken Lusty\n| [[Holden VL Commodore SS Group A]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"